ce:section.ce:para:
Remarkable optical properties of 10 % Co2+-doped CuS QDs have been investigated in order to successfully fabricate UV LEDs. Rather than opting for expensive and cutting-edge LED manufacturing [51,52], we have embraced the open-source, low-cost creation of LED fabrication techniques (details presented in the Supplementary Information). To get starting, a simple everyday battery was connected to this breadboard (Fig. 5
                        a). CIE coordinates of (0.151, 0.08) show an almost pure blue light emission, which demonstrate the good colour purity of the as-prepared phosphor and are close to the standard coordinates from the National Television Standard Committee (NTSC) (0.14, 0.08) (Table 3
                        ) [53]. The swimming pool, indoor room illumination, and other applications may benefit from the uses of these phosphor converted LEDs. But for such applications, experimental efficacy hasn’t been evaluated so far in details.
